277
00:23:35,016 --> 00:23:36,267
Shoko.

278
00:23:42,438 --> 00:23:45,248
Uh, hello. Do you remember me?

279
00:23:45,273 --> 00:23:47,526
We were in elementary school together.

280
00:23:47,557 --> 00:23:49,363
I'm Shoya Ishida.

281
00:23:52,464 --> 00:23:53,097
Oh.

282
00:24:00,788 --> 00:24:02,711
Where are you going? Wait.

283
00:24:08,102 --> 00:24:09,561
Please, come back!

284
00:24:13,137 --> 00:24:14,162
Where'd she go?

285
00:24:15,092 --> 00:24:15,832
Hey!

286
00:24:20,165 --> 00:24:20,940
Hey.

287
00:24:25,351 --> 00:24:27,258
So... I...

288
00:24:31,463 --> 00:24:32,857
I came here to give you this.

289
00:24:32,996 --> 00:24:34,263
I, uh...

290
00:24:35,731 --> 00:24:37,478
You left this behind.

291
00:24:42,455 --> 00:24:45,641
What's that? How do I know sign language?

292
00:24:45,719 --> 00:24:46,842
From a class.

293
00:24:47,306 --> 00:24:49,283
Here you go. It's yours.

294
00:24:53,623 --> 00:24:56,452
I don't even know if you ever wanted to see this again.

295
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,997
I was wondering...

296
00:25:03,824 --> 00:25:07,029
Can me and you, Shoko,

297
00:25:07,266 --> 00:25:09,973
uh... can we be friends?

298
00:25:10,847 --> 00:25:11,848
Is that an opt...

299
00:25:13,485 --> 00:25:15,562
Whoa, what did I just say?

300
00:25:16,174 --> 00:25:19,612
Huh, that's what you were trying to ask me back in school.

301
00:25:19,815 --> 00:25:21,666
I finally understand you.

302
00:25:25,921 --> 00:25:27,271
Don't cry.

303
00:25:28,380 --> 00:25:30,065
Please don't cry, Shoko.

304
00:25:37,466 --> 00:25:39,999
I wanted to ask if we could be friends.

305
00:25:40,479 --> 00:25:41,826
Would that be okay?

306
00:25:43,298 --> 00:25:46,335
Sho-Sho, Sho-Sho.

307
00:25:47,433 --> 00:25:50,543
Sho-Sho, Sho-Sho!

308
00:25:50,904 --> 00:25:52,922
Sho-Sho, wake up!

309
00:25:53,613 --> 00:25:55,517
Time for breakfast!

310
00:26:00,385 --> 00:26:02,735
Okay, Sho, up and at 'em.

311
00:26:05,279 --> 00:26:06,775
Good morning, Maria.

312
00:26:08,213 --> 00:26:09,532
Sho-Sho's awake!

313
00:26:27,560 --> 00:26:28,755
I'm heading out.

314
00:26:29,518 --> 00:26:30,790
Bye-bye, Mommy!

315
00:26:30,814 --> 00:26:31,948
Have a good day, dear.

316
00:26:32,942 --> 00:26:34,998
And breakfast is served.

317
00:26:36,003 --> 00:26:37,888
Thank you for this meal. Mm.

318
00:26:38,186 --> 00:26:39,668
Dig in, big guy.

319
00:26:45,902 --> 00:26:48,614
What's got you so bright and cheery this morning?

320
00:26:49,687 --> 00:26:51,134
Because...

321
00:26:52,362 --> 00:26:53,670
I found this!

322
00:26:53,695 --> 00:26:54,370
Oh.

323
00:26:54,630 --> 00:26:56,893
You've been working so hard at your job,

324
00:26:56,994 --> 00:27:00,419
and you even sold your comics,
your clothes, and your futon.

325
00:27:01,717 --> 00:27:04,894
I am so lucky to have such a thoughtful son.

326
00:27:07,653 --> 00:27:09,730
But tell me, Shoya,

327
00:27:11,198 --> 00:27:13,359
why would you wanna kill yourself?

328
00:27:16,072 --> 00:27:17,509
I just, uh...

329
00:27:17,566 --> 00:27:19,850
I've been going through a lot of crazy stuff lately.

330
00:27:20,411 --> 00:27:22,605
What can I say? I just...

331
00:27:22,630 --> 00:27:23,565
I knew it.

332
00:27:25,597 --> 00:27:27,663
I knew something was going on with you!

333
00:27:27,707 --> 00:27:29,962
Do not even try to deny it!

334
00:27:29,987 --> 00:27:33,129
Your room is clean for a change.
You cancelled your phone service

335
00:27:33,154 --> 00:27:36,738
and everything after April's
been torn off from your calendar!

336
00:27:37,259 --> 00:27:40,519
I can't believe it, it's so morbid.

337
00:27:40,908 --> 00:27:44,201
Promise me you won't go through
with it or I'm torching this.

338
00:27:44,268 --> 00:27:48,128
The 1.7 million yen you earned will go to waste!

339
00:27:50,221 --> 00:27:52,615
Are you listening to a word I'm saying?

340
00:27:53,254 --> 00:27:54,670
Uh, yeah.

341
00:27:55,001 --> 00:27:56,394
Don't do anything crazy, Mom.

342
00:27:56,419 --> 00:27:57,047
Crazy?

343
00:27:57,072 --> 00:27:58,755
You were gonna off yourself!

344
00:27:58,779 --> 00:27:59,753
No, wait!

345
00:27:59,893 --> 00:28:02,198
I'm sorry, Mom. I'm really sorry.

346
00:28:02,236 --> 00:28:04,196
I won't do it again. I swear I won't.

347
00:28:04,221 --> 00:28:05,036
Please don't burn it.

348
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:06,217
What are you not gonna do?

349
00:28:06,242 --> 00:28:07,267
Be specific!

350
00:28:07,418 --> 00:28:09,395
I promise I'm not going to kill myself.

351
00:28:09,581 --> 00:28:12,099
I swear I won't do it. Please believe me.

352
00:28:12,491 --> 00:28:13,565
Do you mean it?

353
00:28:14,134 --> 00:28:15,376
I swear to you.

354
00:28:16,233 --> 00:28:16,986
Okay.

355
00:28:17,631 --> 00:28:19,280
Then I won't burn this.

356
00:28:19,816 --> 00:28:21,043
Mom, watch out!

357
00:28:21,369 --> 00:28:22,675
Ooh, fire!

358
00:28:22,718 --> 00:28:24,882
Ow, my fingers!

359
00:28:25,591 --> 00:28:27,330
Ah, get me some water!

360
00:28:32,554 --> 00:28:34,687
Oh, smokey!

361
00:28:36,384 --> 00:28:40,561
Yesterday, I was planning to jump off
a really tall bridge and kill myself.

362
00:28:41,694 --> 00:28:45,471
I only went to see Shoko
Nishimiya to wrap up any loose ends.

363
00:28:47,462 --> 00:28:51,004
It was hands-down the greatest test of courage ever.

364
00:28:51,737 --> 00:28:53,699
Well, it was supposed to be anyway.

365
00:29:07,502 --> 00:29:09,253
Can we be friends?

366
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:16,067
I'm the world's biggest loser!

367
00:29:16,685 --> 00:29:18,550
On the first day of junior high,

368
00:29:18,945 --> 00:29:21,075
Kazuki made sure everyone knew.

369
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:23,649
You should probably stay away from Shoya Ishida.

370
00:29:23,692 --> 00:29:24,708
He's a bully.

371
00:29:25,433 --> 00:29:28,713
He's so bad, a girl had to switch schools.

372
00:29:32,755 --> 00:29:36,633
Like they always say, what goes around comes around.

373
00:29:37,703 --> 00:29:39,663
I knew I royally screwed up,

374
00:29:40,354 --> 00:29:42,547
and that I needed to pay for being a jerk.

375
00:29:43,928 --> 00:29:47,970
And so, I pushed everyone away.

376
00:30:26,973 --> 00:30:28,291
Alright, everyone.

377
00:30:28,316 --> 00:30:31,593
Make sure to have this translated by next week's class.

378
00:30:41,177 --> 00:30:42,543
Hey, Shoya.

379
00:30:43,069 --> 00:30:45,164
Uh, Miki.

380
00:30:45,232 --> 00:30:47,961
Have you had a chance to hand in your math notebook yet?

381
00:30:48,012 --> 00:30:49,727
Oh, sorry. I forgot.

382
00:30:50,023 --> 00:30:51,038
That's okay.

383
00:30:51,348 --> 00:30:53,293
Just try to hand it in soon, alright?

384
00:30:53,512 --> 00:30:54,128
Sorry.

385
00:30:54,152 --> 00:30:55,120
No problem.

386
00:30:58,759 --> 00:31:00,609
Wanna go sit in the courtyard?

387
00:31:02,138 --> 00:31:04,374
Shoya never hangs out with anyone.

388
00:31:04,592 --> 00:31:05,761
What a loser.

389
00:31:06,276 --> 00:31:09,186
Didn't you hear about him? Everyone knows.

390
00:31:09,559 --> 00:31:11,155
No way, dude!

391
00:31:12,435 --> 00:31:15,077
Hey, check it out. He's looking at us again.

392
00:31:15,741 --> 00:31:18,657
Wonder if he gets lonely being by himself all the time.

393
00:31:19,485 --> 00:31:20,967
What a total freak.

394
00:31:21,545 --> 00:31:23,142
Why does he bother living?

395
00:31:26,791 --> 00:31:29,271
Oh, hey. I got their new album.

396
00:31:29,386 --> 00:31:30,593
You wanna check it out?

397
00:31:30,792 --> 00:31:34,149
Yeah, since you like them, I don't anymore.

398
00:31:34,174 --> 00:31:35,741
Yeah, me too.

399
00:31:40,997 --> 00:31:42,312
Yeah, right.

400
00:32:02,552 --> 00:32:04,496
I've seen that head before.

401
00:32:05,716 --> 00:32:06,940
Who is he?

402
00:32:10,729 --> 00:32:11,407
Uh.

403
00:32:17,776 --> 00:32:19,125
It doesn't matter.

404
00:32:20,296 --> 00:32:22,178
Should I go and see Shoko again?

405
00:32:23,176 --> 00:32:25,265
She said she feeds the koi bread.

406
00:32:26,219 --> 00:32:30,049
But I can't just show up there.
Not after everything I've done.

407
00:32:32,013 --> 00:32:34,680
Should I go and apologize for making her cry?

408
00:32:35,621 --> 00:32:37,971
She did say she's there every Tuesday.

409
00:32:38,864 --> 00:32:40,475
Or is it too creepy?

410
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:40,895
Huh?

411
00:32:52,901 --> 00:32:54,895
Hey, Mom. I'm home.

412
00:33:05,392 --> 00:33:06,853
Hi, Sho.

413
00:33:08,344 --> 00:33:10,411
You scared the crap out of me. What's up?

414
00:33:13,574 --> 00:33:15,953
Uh, I... I'm sorry.

415
00:33:16,151 --> 00:33:18,592
For burning all your hard-earned money.

416
00:33:19,058 --> 00:33:20,479
I didn't mean to.

417
00:33:20,624 --> 00:33:21,612
Uh...

418
00:33:21,984 --> 00:33:25,946
But then again, you only earned
that money so you could kill yourself.

419
00:33:26,259 --> 00:33:27,846
So I don't want it anyway.

420
00:33:29,546 --> 00:33:31,785
Sorry, Mom. I'll earn it back.

421
00:33:32,297 --> 00:33:33,874
I know you will!

422
00:33:33,917 --> 00:33:36,093
But I don't want you to worry too much about it.

423
00:33:36,187 --> 00:33:38,280
In the meantime, how 'bout some dinner?

424
00:33:38,306 --> 00:33:38,982
Who's hungry?

425
00:33:39,007 --> 00:33:40,823
Ooh, ooh, I'm hungry!

426
00:33:50,590 --> 00:33:51,666
Tuesday.

427
00:33:56,940 --> 00:33:59,360
Hey, let me borrow your bike.

428
00:33:59,750 --> 00:34:00,706
Who, me?

429
00:34:00,881 --> 00:34:02,797
Huh? What do you need my bicycle for?

430
00:34:02,822 --> 00:34:04,190
That kid I saw at lunch.

431
00:34:04,233 --> 00:34:06,273
I forgot something at home so

432
00:34:06,327 --> 00:34:07,637
I need your bike to get it.

433
00:34:07,661 --> 00:34:08,107
What?

434
00:34:08,132 --> 00:34:09,699
But I don't even know you.

435
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,754
Why can't you just use your own bike?

436
00:34:13,155 --> 00:34:16,002
I'm asking you because I don't have one.

437
00:34:16,420 --> 00:34:18,501
No, please don't.

438
00:34:18,552 --> 00:34:19,467
Give it up, fatso.

439
00:34:19,492 --> 00:34:20,181
Wait, stop.

440
00:34:20,276 --> 00:34:22,868
I'm being robbed! Somebody help me!

441
00:34:24,460 --> 00:34:26,796
Anybody out there!

442
00:34:26,821 --> 00:34:28,823
Why won't anyone help me?

443
00:34:28,930 --> 00:34:29,988
Shut up!

444
00:34:30,423 --> 00:34:32,030
God, you're annoying.

445
00:34:33,530 --> 00:34:35,936
Just let go of the damn bike already!

446
00:34:35,961 --> 00:34:36,864
Hey, uh...

447
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:37,581
What?

448
00:34:37,691 --> 00:34:40,536
Do you wanna borrow mine? It's over there.

449
00:34:40,643 --> 00:34:42,728
Yeah? Thanks man.

450
00:34:42,841 --> 00:34:44,336
You're a godsend.

451
00:34:47,973 --> 00:34:49,625
Of course he stole it.

452
00:34:51,193 --> 00:34:53,002
And today's Tuesday.

453
00:34:53,717 --> 00:34:54,895
Of all days.

454
00:34:55,341 --> 00:34:58,238
So is that a sign that I should just leave her alone?

455
00:34:58,897 --> 00:35:03,259
It's not like I can't just walk there,
but it's like I'm being told not to go.

456
00:35:04,719 --> 00:35:06,247
I need a good reason.

457
00:35:07,644 --> 00:35:08,269
Huh?

458
00:35:10,426 --> 00:35:11,950
Something real.

459
00:35:13,825 --> 00:35:16,115
So it doesn't look like I'm trying too hard.

460
00:35:22,050 --> 00:35:24,041
Half off fluffy new bread.

461
00:35:24,990 --> 00:35:25,855
This is it!

462
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:29,353
Is Shoko Nishimiya here?

463
00:35:29,449 --> 00:35:30,560
She's not here.

464
00:35:31,109 --> 00:35:32,588
She's right there.

465
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:33,962
Not her.

466
00:35:35,020 --> 00:35:37,989
There's nobody here named Shoko.

467
00:35:38,171 --> 00:35:40,136
Who are you anyway?

468
00:35:40,161 --> 00:35:43,109
I mean, are you actually a friend of hers?

469
00:35:43,898 --> 00:35:44,984
Thought so.

470
00:35:51,654 --> 00:35:53,137
Nothing to worry about.

471
00:35:54,580 --> 00:35:56,914
There was a rat in the hallway.

472
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,073
A really gross one.

473
00:36:01,976 --> 00:36:04,354
Don't worry. He won't be back.

474
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:14,359
Can we be friends?

475
00:36:27,862 --> 00:36:30,516
Huh? What the...?

476
00:36:32,077 --> 00:36:33,923
Oh, found him!

477
00:36:33,948 --> 00:36:36,640
Hey, you! Over here!

478
00:36:36,665 --> 00:36:39,193
Look, check it out. I found your bike.

479
00:36:39,265 --> 00:36:40,752
This is yours, isn't it?

480
00:36:42,776 --> 00:36:44,543
What perfect timing!

481
00:36:44,628 --> 00:36:47,264
Oh, it's a good thing you had your address on it.

482
00:36:48,354 --> 00:36:49,352
That's great.

483
00:36:50,008 --> 00:36:51,481
But where did you find it?

484
00:36:51,574 --> 00:36:54,035
That jerk dumped it in a rice field.

485
00:36:54,061 --> 00:36:56,403
Man, it took me forever to find it.

486
00:36:56,623 --> 00:36:58,047
Thank goodness I did.

487
00:36:58,411 --> 00:36:59,994
And I found you, too.

488
00:37:06,903 --> 00:37:08,576
Is something wrong?

489
00:37:08,849 --> 00:37:10,551
What? Nothing.

490
00:37:10,941 --> 00:37:13,381
Tell me. What's your name, anyway?

491
00:37:13,455 --> 00:37:16,096
But, you don't already know?

492
00:37:16,121 --> 00:37:19,301
Tomohiro Nagatsuka. I sit behind you.

493
00:37:20,281 --> 00:37:21,876
Right, I knew that.

494
00:37:22,429 --> 00:37:25,146
It's really good bread. You wanna split it with me?

495
00:37:25,434 --> 00:37:26,393
Shoya!

496
00:37:27,734 --> 00:37:29,040
Hey there, Shoya.

497
00:37:30,265 --> 00:37:31,432
Good morning.

498
00:37:31,523 --> 00:37:33,583
Uh, morning.

499
00:37:36,315 --> 00:37:37,622
Hey, Shoya.

500
00:37:37,894 --> 00:37:40,306
Do you wanna hang out with me after school today?

501
00:37:40,423 --> 00:37:42,312
I mean, since we're friends now.

502
00:37:43,278 --> 00:37:44,794
Shoya, over here!

503
00:37:44,845 --> 00:37:46,171
I saved you a seat!

504
00:38:08,738 --> 00:38:10,471
What's troubling you, Yasho?

505
00:38:11,176 --> 00:38:13,471
Huh? It's nothing.

506
00:38:13,743 --> 00:38:14,673
Who's Yasho?

507
00:38:14,697 --> 00:38:15,612
It's your nickname.

508
00:38:15,637 --> 00:38:16,725
Shows that we're close.

509
00:38:16,749 --> 00:38:17,863
Oh, cool.

510
00:38:19,914 --> 00:38:22,321
Well, so tell me what's troubling you?

511
00:38:22,404 --> 00:38:25,670
You know you can tell me anything.
That's what best friends are for.

512
00:38:29,869 --> 00:38:32,228
Hey, do you mind if I ask you something?

513
00:38:32,855 --> 00:38:35,369
What does it mean to become someone's friend?

514
00:38:35,965 --> 00:38:39,937
Like, is there some sort of
friendship process you go through?

515
00:38:40,261 --> 00:38:43,052
Or like, do you need any specific qualifications?

516
00:38:44,305 --> 00:38:45,922
'Ey, Yasho.

517
00:38:49,678 --> 00:38:51,053
Give me ya hand, 'kay?

518
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:56,803
'Ey, 'ey.

519
00:39:04,222 --> 00:39:06,380
Now you and I is friends.

520
00:39:06,579 --> 00:39:08,689
It can be as simple as that, see.

521
00:39:08,929 --> 00:39:12,367
Friendship don't gotta do with no rules or qualifications,

522
00:39:12,411 --> 00:39:14,181
'cause it's about something deeper.

523
00:39:14,465 --> 00:39:17,275
A bond. And ya just can't break that.

524
00:39:18,505 --> 00:39:19,303
Capiche?

525
00:39:21,736 --> 00:39:23,357
She's not here.

526
00:39:23,701 --> 00:39:24,898
She's right there.

527
00:39:24,922 --> 00:39:25,750
She's not.

528
00:39:26,570 --> 00:39:31,100
Listen, I think maybe... Shoko's my girlfriend, okay?

529
00:39:32,996 --> 00:39:34,825
Oh, well, that sucks.

530
00:39:34,942 --> 00:39:36,827
Uh, not for me personally,

531
00:39:36,957 --> 00:39:38,533
because I brought her all this bread.

532
00:39:38,985 --> 00:39:42,767
But... I-I didn't know that Shoko was into younger guys.

533
00:39:42,902 --> 00:39:46,013
I mean, nothing against you. I
just never would have guessed.

534
00:39:46,224 --> 00:39:47,976
Can you at least give her the bread?

535
00:39:48,001 --> 00:39:48,527
It's really good.

536
00:39:48,551 --> 00:39:49,005
Listen.

537
00:39:49,492 --> 00:39:53,811
If you're just here to make yourself
feel better, you might as well leave.

538
00:39:57,496 --> 00:40:00,802
If you'll excuse me, goodbye.

539
00:40:01,528 --> 00:40:03,027
Listen, boy!

540
00:40:03,281 --> 00:40:04,245
What's your problem?

541
00:40:04,270 --> 00:40:05,977
My friend here just wants to see Miss Shoko.

542
00:40:06,002 --> 00:40:06,484
'Kay?

543
00:40:06,508 --> 00:40:07,202
Where'd you come from?

544
00:40:07,227 --> 00:40:09,542
So stop being so stubborn and go get her!

545
00:40:09,567 --> 00:40:11,807
Seriously, what are you even doing here?

546
00:40:11,901 --> 00:40:12,462
Ugh!

547
00:40:12,856 --> 00:40:15,762
I followed you. Friends have each other's backs.

548
00:40:16,548 --> 00:40:19,351
The shitty stalker has his own shitty stalker.

