01:12:10,314 --> 01:12:11,967
Dude, I was just being friendly.

1092
01:12:13,597 --> 01:12:15,574
Well, go be friendly with someone else!

1093
01:12:15,599 --> 01:12:17,932
Oh, Nagatsuka, you really crack me up.

1094
01:12:17,957 --> 01:12:20,275
Yasho is my friend! I've got my eye on you.

1095
01:12:20,300 --> 01:12:20,868
You better watch it!

1096
01:12:20,893 --> 01:12:22,802
Hey is that your real hair?

1097
01:12:23,621 --> 01:12:25,101
Knock it off, will ya?

1098
01:12:25,126 --> 01:12:26,780
I'm not joking!

1099
01:12:26,854 --> 01:12:27,865
What's so funny?

1100
01:12:27,926 --> 01:12:29,250
What is this?

1101
01:12:29,841 --> 01:12:31,209
Faster, Satoshi!

1102
01:12:31,234 --> 01:12:32,113
They're catching up!

1103
01:12:32,137 --> 01:12:33,105
We can do this, Yasho!

1104
01:12:33,149 --> 01:12:34,368
Come on, pedal harder!

1105
01:12:34,393 --> 01:12:35,302
What is this?

1106
01:12:36,720 --> 01:12:37,713
Is it okay?

1107
01:12:38,431 --> 01:12:40,658
Am I allowed to have this much fun?

1108
01:12:41,639 --> 01:12:44,155
This feels so... familiar.

1109
01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:45,192
Ow, ooh.

1110
01:12:46,164 --> 01:12:47,143
Great catch, buddy.

1111
01:12:47,168 --> 01:12:47,824
Oh, yeah.

1112
01:12:48,802 --> 01:12:52,371
It almost feels like... like we're all friends.

1113
01:12:57,900 --> 01:12:58,870
Hey, Shoya.

1114
01:12:58,894 --> 01:12:59,654
Uh... huh?

1115
01:12:59,903 --> 01:13:02,656
I'm hungry. I feel like some takoyaki.

1116
01:13:02,681 --> 01:13:03,802
Come with me to get some.

1117
01:13:03,827 --> 01:13:06,188
Uh, I'm not... h-hey, wait!

1118
01:13:07,808 --> 01:13:10,432
Here you go. One takoyaki.

1119
01:13:10,457 --> 01:13:11,466
Huh, thank you.

1120
01:13:11,537 --> 01:13:12,529
And Naoka,

1121
01:13:13,329 --> 01:13:15,793
you need to learn how to mind your own business.

1122
01:13:23,365 --> 01:13:26,230
Kazuki?

1123
01:13:29,814 --> 01:13:30,728
Huh?

1124
01:13:31,598 --> 01:13:33,211
Shoya, where are you going?

1125
01:13:35,820 --> 01:13:37,604
I'll text you later, okay?

1126
01:13:38,649 --> 01:13:39,900
Hey, wait up!

1127
01:13:41,391 --> 01:13:42,609
Are you mad at me?

1128
01:13:43,175 --> 01:13:44,494
No, I'm not.

1129
01:13:45,308 --> 01:13:46,853
I'm fine. Yeah.

1130
01:13:47,503 --> 01:13:50,766
I just thought maybe you guys could be friends.

1131
01:13:50,891 --> 01:13:52,639
You know, like you used to be.

1132
01:13:53,399 --> 01:13:57,937
I guess I was hoping once you guys actually
saw each other, everything would be okay.

1133
01:13:58,036 --> 01:13:59,951
Don't do me any favors, okay?

1134
01:14:01,411 --> 01:14:01,871
Uh.

1135
01:14:03,804 --> 01:14:04,472
Wait.

1136
01:14:05,832 --> 01:14:07,940
I did the exact same thing.

1137
01:14:13,031 --> 01:14:15,367
You and I are more alike than you think, you know?

1138
01:14:15,528 --> 01:14:16,729
No, we're not.

1139
01:14:16,861 --> 01:14:17,857
Yes, we are.

1140
01:14:18,457 --> 01:14:19,792
We're nothing alike.

1141
01:14:23,781 --> 01:14:25,609
You know, if Shoko hadn't shown up,

1142
01:14:25,652 --> 01:14:27,837
we would all still be friends and be happy.

1143
01:14:30,219 --> 01:14:31,568
You don't know that.

1144
01:14:31,658 --> 01:14:33,470
Oh, come on, just admit it.

1145
01:14:33,765 --> 01:14:35,271
If it wasn't for her,

1146
01:14:35,314 --> 01:14:37,985
things wouldn't have gotten
all weird between Miyoko and me.

1147
01:14:38,709 --> 01:14:41,450
And then you wouldn't have stopped
being friends with Kazuki, either.

1148
01:14:42,823 --> 01:14:46,115
I just wanna go back to the way
things were before she showed up.

1149
01:14:46,140 --> 01:14:48,733
Kazuki and I... that was me.

1150
01:14:48,936 --> 01:14:50,634
I ruined that all on my own.

1151
01:14:51,500 --> 01:14:53,287
Shoya, tell me the truth.

1152
01:14:53,463 --> 01:14:54,594
Do you hate me?

1153
01:14:54,638 --> 01:14:55,555
Probably.

1154
01:14:57,817 --> 01:15:00,412
Fine. Time for a ride on the Ferris wheel!

1155
01:15:00,774 --> 01:15:02,893
I'll go see if Shoko wants to come with me.

1156
01:15:03,148 --> 01:15:03,801
Hey.

1157
01:15:04,430 --> 01:15:04,918
Huh?

1158
01:15:05,256 --> 01:15:08,244
Hey, Shoko, you gotta come ride the Ferris wheel with me.

1159
01:15:08,370 --> 01:15:09,622
Cut it out, Naoka.

1160
01:15:09,763 --> 01:15:12,097
If you guys are going, can you take my camera?

1161
01:15:12,284 --> 01:15:14,579
I wanna ride that roller coaster again.

1162
01:15:38,657 --> 01:15:41,268
Oh, hi, Yuzuru. Come on in.

1163
01:15:41,320 --> 01:15:42,917
Shoya's upstairs in his room.

1164
01:15:43,863 --> 01:15:44,429
Whoa.

1165
01:15:45,004 --> 01:15:46,944
Got a top-secret video for you.

1166
01:15:48,344 --> 01:15:50,476
A video from the Ferris wheel?

1167
01:15:50,520 --> 01:15:50,997
Yup.

1168
01:15:51,665 --> 01:15:53,014
How'd you get it?

1169
01:15:53,131 --> 01:15:53,993
Spying.

1170
01:15:54,057 --> 01:15:54,705
What?

1171
01:15:59,877 --> 01:16:01,835
I want you to listen to me carefully.

1172
01:16:02,532 --> 01:16:03,794
I hate you.

1173
01:16:03,883 --> 01:16:06,401
Uh, oh.

1174
01:16:08,393 --> 01:16:09,899
Put that thing away.

1175
01:16:10,303 --> 01:16:13,256
I'm going to speak slowly so you can understand,

1176
01:16:13,458 --> 01:16:15,664
and I'll listen to everything you have to say.

1177
01:16:18,025 --> 01:16:20,444
I'll admit that in elementary school,

1178
01:16:20,469 --> 01:16:23,377
I had no idea what things were like for you,

1179
01:16:23,807 --> 01:16:27,164
but it's not like you tried to
understand what I was going through either.

1180
01:16:27,401 --> 01:16:28,552
Know what I mean?

1181
01:16:28,982 --> 01:16:31,942
And instead of getting a clue like a normal person,

1182
01:16:31,967 --> 01:16:35,223
you just kept giving me that stupid notebook of yours.

1183
01:16:35,303 --> 01:16:39,946
You were always being so weird, and you
would apologize all the time for everything.

1184
01:16:40,073 --> 01:16:41,968
So I tried a different approach.

1185
01:16:42,006 --> 01:16:43,877
I ignored you and blew you off.

1186
01:16:43,940 --> 01:16:47,084
That was my way of telling you
that I didn't wanna hang out with you.

1187
01:16:47,286 --> 01:16:52,040
But nope, you just kept coming around
with your stupid book and your stupid signs.

1188
01:16:52,163 --> 01:16:53,599
You're so clueless.

1189
01:16:53,689 --> 01:16:56,495
Then you had to go run crying to the grown-ups.

1190
01:16:56,599 --> 01:16:58,350
You got Shoya in trouble.

1191
01:16:58,735 --> 01:17:02,378
And that's how he ended up losing
every single one of his friends.

1192
01:17:02,451 --> 01:17:05,259
You pretty much ruined everything for everyone.

1193
01:17:05,341 --> 01:17:06,732
You get that, right?

1194
01:17:08,380 --> 01:17:09,620
I'm sorry.

1195
01:17:09,947 --> 01:17:11,517
God, you still don't get it.

1196
01:17:11,601 --> 01:17:14,027
I'm not looking for another apology from you.

1197
01:17:14,626 --> 01:17:16,454
We were both going through a lot,

1198
01:17:16,639 --> 01:17:19,622
and I don't think either of us
could have done anything differently.

1199
01:17:20,299 --> 01:17:21,099
But still,

1200
01:17:21,413 --> 01:17:23,960
it's not like I wanna be your new best friend or anything.

1201
01:17:24,247 --> 01:17:26,282
I mean, I still hate you a lot,

1202
01:17:26,526 --> 01:17:28,914
and I'm pretty sure you hate me too, right?

1203
01:17:29,386 --> 01:17:32,696
So, why don't we stop pretending
we're something we're not, okay?

1204
01:17:32,962 --> 01:17:33,991
Let's shake on it.

1205
01:17:34,324 --> 01:17:36,012
From one hater to another.

1206
01:17:37,669 --> 01:17:39,381
But you're wrong.

1207
01:17:39,537 --> 01:17:41,178
I don't hate you.

1208
01:17:41,600 --> 01:17:44,677
I-I hate myself.

1209
01:17:44,702 --> 01:17:46,180
What did you say?

1210
01:17:46,394 --> 01:17:50,139
What did you say?!

1211
01:17:52,279 --> 01:17:54,667
Well? What are you gonna do?

1212
01:17:55,047 --> 01:17:56,901
You gonna say sorry again?

1213
01:17:57,359 --> 01:18:00,855
It's been five years and you haven't changed a bit.

1214
01:18:00,906 --> 01:18:04,122
You still have no intention of being real with me.

1215
01:18:09,420 --> 01:18:10,327
What do you think?

1216
01:18:10,936 --> 01:18:13,457
Oh, it's uh...

1217
01:18:17,016 --> 01:18:18,000
All I want...

1218
01:18:19,464 --> 01:18:21,423
is for Shoko to like herself.

1219
01:18:30,591 --> 01:18:32,365
Are you sure it was Naoka?

1220
01:18:32,390 --> 01:18:33,826
Yeah, it was her.

1221
01:18:34,601 --> 01:18:37,735
Is there really a lot of bad blood between her and Shoko?

1222
01:18:37,786 --> 01:18:39,309
Uh, why do you ask?

1223
01:18:40,093 --> 01:18:43,422
Miki said something serious went down at your old school.

1224
01:18:44,824 --> 01:18:46,945
Shoko's hearing is really bad.

1225
01:18:46,970 --> 01:18:49,431
I mean, she can barely hear anything, right?

1226
01:18:50,315 --> 01:18:50,862
Yeah.

1227
01:18:51,399 --> 01:18:55,831
It just occurred to me, maybe that's why she
kept getting bullied all the time, you know?

1228
01:18:57,328 --> 01:18:59,707
You'd have to be a major douche bag.

1229
01:19:00,026 --> 01:19:01,687
Who bullies a deaf kid?

1230
01:19:02,019 --> 01:19:03,979
What's wrong with people, right?

1231
01:19:04,514 --> 01:19:05,819
What are you saying?

1232
01:19:05,883 --> 01:19:09,000
Wait, you think I'm spreading rumors
about what happened in elementary school?

1233
01:19:09,024 --> 01:19:11,724
Shh, will you keep it down? The whole school can hear you.

1234
01:19:13,699 --> 01:19:16,956
I really wanted to believe that
you had actually changed, Shoya.

1235
01:19:17,000 --> 01:19:19,854
But you are still the same awful
person you were in elementary school!

1236
01:19:19,878 --> 01:19:20,620
You okay, Yasho?

1237
01:19:20,645 --> 01:19:22,479
Can you just please calm down a second?

1238
01:19:22,981 --> 01:19:24,417
Hey, guys, what's going on?

1239
01:19:24,442 --> 01:19:26,689
Remember when I told you Shoko was bullied?

1240
01:19:26,735 --> 01:19:29,665
Well, it was Shoya! He was the one who used to bully her!

1241
01:19:32,175 --> 01:19:34,117
How can you say that, Miki?

1242
01:19:34,746 --> 01:19:35,932
Yasho would never do that.

1243
01:19:35,975 --> 01:19:37,814
Why would I make up something like that?

1244
01:19:39,028 --> 01:19:41,331
But you used to make fun of her too, Miki.

1245
01:19:41,530 --> 01:19:45,198
I never, ever said anything horrible behind Shoko's back.

1246
01:19:45,223 --> 01:19:46,904
What? You picked on Shoko?

1247
01:19:46,970 --> 01:19:47,972
Yeah, it was him!

1248
01:19:47,997 --> 01:19:50,434
He was the one who made Shoko's life a living hell.

1249
01:19:52,548 --> 01:19:53,799
It was so awful.

1250
01:19:53,950 --> 01:19:56,362
I kept begging him to leave her alone,

1251
01:19:56,698 --> 01:19:58,930
but Shoya never listens to anyone.

1252
01:19:59,429 --> 01:20:01,072
I was so scared of him.

1253
01:20:03,988 --> 01:20:07,223
Yasho, what's wrong?

1254
01:20:07,732 --> 01:20:08,955
Sorry, gotta go.

1255
01:20:08,979 --> 01:20:09,800
Are you okay?

1256
01:20:11,957 --> 01:20:13,537
Hey, Yasho!

1257
01:20:42,068 --> 01:20:44,918
Yeah, I hate me too.

1258
01:20:56,315 --> 01:20:58,038
Hey, we're over here!

1259
01:20:58,063 --> 01:20:58,737
Hi!

1260
01:21:00,903 --> 01:21:02,069
Is something wrong?

1261
01:21:03,796 --> 01:21:05,303
Oh, no, not really.

1262
01:21:06,326 --> 01:21:07,507
It's nothing.

1263
01:21:07,531 --> 01:21:07,912
Oh.

1264
01:21:09,325 --> 01:21:11,427
There he is, my main man!

1265
01:21:11,666 --> 01:21:13,611
I brought your backpack for you.

1266
01:21:13,745 --> 01:21:14,787
Hey, guys.

1267
01:21:14,811 --> 01:21:15,778
Naoka?

1268
01:21:16,785 --> 01:21:18,195
I asked her to come.

1269
01:21:22,229 --> 01:21:24,100
I'm sorry about what happened.

1270
01:21:25,171 --> 01:21:26,215
But, well...

1271
01:21:26,778 --> 01:21:29,607
you were the one who started causing all that trouble.

1272
01:21:30,133 --> 01:21:31,458
The thing is,

1273
01:21:31,938 --> 01:21:37,210
Satoshi said I should go ahead and forgive you
since you've been trying to make things right with Shoko.

1274
01:21:38,067 --> 01:21:42,114
Are you kidding me? This is wrong on so many levels.

1275
01:21:42,166 --> 01:21:44,582
You can't blame everything that happened on Shoya.

1276
01:21:44,739 --> 01:21:45,994
We were all guilty.

1277
01:21:47,243 --> 01:21:47,983
We?

1278
01:21:48,673 --> 01:21:50,237
But, Nao, that isn't true.

1279
01:21:50,262 --> 01:21:51,053
What's not?

1280
01:21:52,034 --> 01:21:56,895
I never made fun of Shoko or did anything
to bully her the way the rest of you guys did.

1281
01:21:57,247 --> 01:21:58,935
Don't lump me in with you!

1282
01:22:00,219 --> 01:22:01,345
Naoka.

1283
01:22:02,315 --> 01:22:03,855
Oh...

1284
01:22:04,645 --> 01:22:06,090
Hm, you're right.

1285
01:22:06,413 --> 01:22:08,909
You and I are completely different.

1286
01:22:09,002 --> 01:22:11,570
You just sat back and laughed along with everyone else.

1287
01:22:11,914 --> 01:22:12,932
Did not!

1288
01:22:13,049 --> 01:22:14,530
Just ask Miyoko.

1289
01:22:15,165 --> 01:22:16,309
What, me?

1290
01:22:16,540 --> 01:22:19,757
Naoka used to talk about you
behind your back all the time, too!

1291
01:22:19,782 --> 01:22:21,937
I just said what everyone else was thinking.

1292
01:22:23,446 --> 01:22:25,953
Well, Miyoko, wanna weigh in?

1293
01:22:26,721 --> 01:22:29,528
Uh, to be completely honest,

1294
01:22:29,845 --> 01:22:33,413
back then, I was... I was scared of both of you.

1295
01:22:33,438 --> 01:22:35,525
What? Whose side are you on anyway?

1296
01:22:35,550 --> 01:22:37,119
I'm not on anyone's side.

1297
01:22:37,199 --> 01:22:38,152
Just stop.

1298
01:22:39,824 --> 01:22:41,257
It was my fault, okay?

1299
01:22:41,642 --> 01:22:42,877
It's all my fault.

1300
01:22:44,668 --> 01:22:46,507
I can't stand martyrs.

1301
01:22:48,964 --> 01:22:50,254
That's enough, Naoka.

1302
01:22:51,016 --> 01:22:53,683
Stop trying to drag everybody else down to your level.

1303
01:22:53,889 --> 01:22:55,410
That was harsh. You didn't have to p...

1304
01:22:55,435 --> 01:22:56,829
Oh, please, Miyoko.

1305
01:22:57,203 --> 01:23:00,257
We all know that you just run
away whenever things get tense.

1306
01:23:00,938 --> 01:23:01,939
Shoya.

1307
01:23:02,104 --> 01:23:03,033
What's gotten into you?

1308
01:23:03,057 --> 01:23:06,119
God, will you just stop talking?

1309
01:23:06,683 --> 01:23:09,048
You really love the sound of your own voice, don't you?

1310
01:23:10,147 --> 01:23:13,555
Listen, man. No matter what
anyone says, I've got your back.

1311
01:23:13,798 --> 01:23:15,357
I don't care.

1312
01:23:15,682 --> 01:23:17,336
Will you just back off?

1313
01:23:17,519 --> 01:23:18,607
You hardly know me.

1314
01:23:18,632 --> 01:23:20,186
I can't take this anymore.

1315
01:23:20,211 --> 01:23:21,661
I'm not staying here!

1316
01:23:22,015 --> 01:23:24,735
It's alright, you don't mean it.

1317
01:23:25,204 --> 01:23:27,425
But I'm gonna give you some space.

1318
01:23:29,861 --> 01:23:31,075
Hey, Shoko.

1319
01:23:32,375 --> 01:23:32,997
Later.

1320
01:23:39,504 --> 01:23:40,982
I'm sorry, Shoya.

1321
01:23:42,605 --> 01:23:45,089
I never should have agreed to come here to begin with.

1322
01:23:48,062 --> 01:23:50,987
That's not cool. You were way too harsh.

1323
01:23:52,447 --> 01:23:55,442
What do you know? You're not
even really part of our group.

1324
01:23:56,415 --> 01:23:57,967
I thought we were friends.

1325
01:24:11,176 --> 01:24:12,210
Almost forgot.

1326
01:24:13,465 --> 01:24:15,007
So, starting next week,

1327
01:24:15,511 --> 01:24:17,093
it's summer vacation.

1328
01:24:17,882 --> 01:24:20,050
Do you wanna go somewhere special?

1329
01:24:41,089 --> 01:24:44,387
You're going to ruin your eyes
reading in the dark like that.

1330
01:24:50,416 --> 01:24:51,417
Here.

1331
01:24:58,182 --> 01:25:01,838
You spend so much time worried about your big sister.

1332
01:25:04,333 --> 01:25:07,314
Now I'm starting to worry about you, sweetie.

1333
01:25:07,911 --> 01:25:10,844
You get so caught up in Shoko's life,

1334
01:25:10,883 --> 01:25:13,305
that you never leave any time for yourself.

1335
01:25:13,330 --> 01:25:16,116
I could say the same thing about you, Granny.

1336
01:25:16,227 --> 01:25:20,230
Instead of going to the senior center,
all you do is study sign language.

1337
01:25:20,839 --> 01:25:24,469
That's something I'm doing for
myself, so that doesn't really count.

1338
01:25:24,629 --> 01:25:28,559
What a coincidence, because I'm
doing all these things for myself, too.

1339
01:25:29,796 --> 01:25:30,507
Really?

1340
01:25:34,440 --> 01:25:36,432
You are such a good kid.

1341
01:25:36,920 --> 01:25:37,959
You think so?

1342
01:25:38,130 --> 01:25:43,120
Mom chews me out on a daily basis, and
I haven't gone to school in like weeks.

1343
01:25:43,493 --> 01:25:46,145
Yes, sweetie, but you've got a heart of gold.

1344
01:25:46,699 --> 01:25:48,875
Shoko's no slouch, either.

1345
01:25:50,847 --> 01:25:53,589
I've got some mighty fine grandchildren.

1346
01:25:58,163 --> 01:25:59,977
Have one of the mochi, too.

1347
01:26:00,298 --> 01:26:01,360
You've got it!

1348
01:26:16,525 --> 01:26:17,182
Granny.

1349
01:26:30,316 --> 01:26:32,191
Hey there, Shoko.

1350
01:26:32,526 --> 01:26:35,756
So today, I was able to score us some really great bread.

1351
01:26:35,917 --> 01:26:36,569
See?

1352
01:26:37,450 --> 01:26:39,200
It's awesome, like you're awesome.

1353
01:26:39,598 --> 01:26:40,120
Um.

1354
01:26:41,024 --> 01:26:43,496
Like really great bread is awesome.

1355
01:26:43,521 --> 01:26:45,787
This loaf here is just like you.

1356
01:26:46,831 --> 01:26:48,728
Well, that makes no sense.

1357
01:26:49,622 --> 01:26:50,132
Uh.

1358
01:26:52,056 --> 01:26:53,824
I wonder if she's coming today.

1359
01:26:57,319 --> 01:26:58,180
Guess not.

1360
01:26:59,073 --> 01:27:01,320
Is your stomach bothering you?

1361
01:27:02,219 --> 01:27:03,337
Is that too personal?

1362
01:27:12,959 --> 01:27:13,873
Hey!

1363
01:27:14,362 --> 01:27:15,157
Yuzu...!

1364
01:27:29,297 --> 01:27:30,428
Oh, I should go.

1365
01:27:30,512 --> 01:27:31,421
Shoya.

1366
01:27:31,445 --> 01:27:31,846
Huh?

1367
01:27:32,147 --> 01:27:32,880
Hey there.

1368
01:27:33,119 --> 01:27:34,555
What the heck are you wearing?

1369
01:27:34,783 --> 01:27:37,091
What's it look like? My uniform.

1370
01:27:37,165 --> 01:27:38,793
What do you think? Ya like?

1371
01:27:38,846 --> 01:27:40,081
Why are you wearing it?

1372
01:27:40,106 --> 01:27:42,268
For school, duh.

1373
01:27:42,621 --> 01:27:45,513
Uh, but we're on summer break right now.

1374
01:27:46,736 --> 01:27:48,662
So what's really going on?

1375
01:27:50,974 --> 01:27:52,829
Nothing is going on, I swear.

1376
01:27:53,001 --> 01:27:55,619
If anyone asks, tell 'em I'm cosplaying.

1377
01:27:56,112 --> 01:27:56,672
Uh.

1378
01:27:58,102 --> 01:28:00,915
That was from my sister so I better take off.

1379
01:28:00,940 --> 01:28:02,366
Where to? I'll walk you there.

1380
01:28:02,466 --> 01:28:03,641
What? No, it's fine.

1381
01:28:03,746 --> 01:28:04,801
You sure you're okay?

1382
01:28:05,048 --> 01:28:06,740
Yeah, everything's cool.

1383
01:28:07,269 --> 01:28:08,977
Then why were you crying just now?

1384
01:28:09,709 --> 01:28:10,424
Come on.

1385
01:28:13,237 --> 01:28:16,110
This actually doesn't have anything to do with you.

1386
01:28:16,732 --> 01:28:17,776
Sure it does.

1387
01:28:18,496 --> 01:28:20,336
At least, I think so.

1388
01:28:20,810 --> 01:28:21,443
Why?

1389
01:28:22,210 --> 01:28:23,960
I'm just worried about you, okay?

1390
01:28:26,083 --> 01:28:29,118
I don't believe it. You sound just like my grandma.

1391
01:28:30,936 --> 01:28:33,483
Alright, if you wanna come, then come.

1392
01:28:36,994 --> 01:28:37,920
This is it.

1393
01:28:38,400 --> 01:28:39,826
Thanks for walking me.

1394
01:28:40,479 --> 01:28:41,586
I appreciate it.

1395
01:28:44,411 --> 01:28:45,248
See ya.

1396
01:28:51,507 --> 01:28:52,953
Good luck, Yuzuru.

1397
01:28:56,658 --> 01:28:58,780
Shoya, wait.

1398
01:29:01,854 --> 01:29:03,679
Truth is, I'm scared.

1399
01:30:59,109 --> 01:31:00,651
Whoa, that's cool.

1400
01:31:03,184 --> 01:31:05,498
Come on, Shoko. Let's go check it out!

1401
01:31:07,964 --> 01:31:08,549
Uh.

1402
01:31:14,906 --> 01:31:16,091
Shoko?

1403
01:31:18,939 --> 01:31:19,680
Ah!

1404
01:31:24,878 --> 01:31:26,172
I'm fine, really.

1405
01:31:28,536 --> 01:31:30,475
Uh, why are you apologizing?

1406
01:31:36,790 --> 01:31:38,540
That's totally not true.

1407
01:31:38,904 --> 01:31:43,372
Hey, are you busy tomorrow? Let's hang out tomorrow, too.

1408
01:31:47,812 --> 01:31:51,358
Shoko said that I'll be miserable whenever I'm with her.

1409
01:31:54,079 --> 01:31:56,006
But I'm the one who made her unhappy.

1410
01:31:57,183 --> 01:31:58,016
It was me.

1411
01:32:08,336 --> 01:32:11,985
One thing to see

1412
01:32:13,354 --> 01:32:17,455
And to have someone love me

1413
01:32:18,593 --> 01:32:21,660
Even monsters feel

1414
01:32:22,894 --> 01:32:24,684
In their heart

1415
01:32:27,447 --> 01:32:29,925
There's no going back to the way things were.

1416
01:32:35,245 --> 01:32:39,142
Hey, Shoko! Cool. I see Yuzuru's gonna tag along with us.

1417
01:32:39,168 --> 01:32:40,275
Let's check out a movie.

1418
01:32:41,832 --> 01:32:43,346
This is hilarious!

1419
01:32:43,493 --> 01:32:45,822
Hey, greetings, classmates!

1420
01:32:45,924 --> 01:32:47,355
I gotta say,

1421
01:32:47,455 --> 01:32:49,551
this has been the best summer break ever!

1422
01:32:49,612 --> 01:32:50,753
Just ask Yuzuru.

1423
01:32:50,777 --> 01:32:51,673
Whatever.

1424
01:32:51,727 --> 01:32:54,442
Seriously, we're having an absolute blast!

1425
01:32:54,467 --> 01:32:57,143
What about tomorrow? We should go somewhere fun!

1426
01:32:57,343 --> 01:32:59,029
Any ideas where we should go?

1427
01:32:59,087 --> 01:33:01,782
Sorry, but we already have plans for tomorrow.

1428
01:33:02,499 --> 01:33:02,977
Hmm?

1429
01:33:04,778 --> 01:33:06,557
Huh? No way! Are you insane?

1430
01:33:06,582 --> 01:33:07,757
She wants to make what?

1431
01:33:07,906 --> 01:33:09,045
You sure it's okay?

1432
01:33:09,737 --> 01:33:11,627
I feel like I really shouldn't be here.

1433
01:33:11,740 --> 01:33:16,805
Your mission, should you choose to accept it, is
to assist us in baking our mother's birthday cake.

1434
01:33:17,397 --> 01:33:19,047
Are you absolutely sure?

1435
01:33:19,534 --> 01:33:20,840
I don't wanna get hit again.

1436
01:33:20,865 --> 01:33:21,996
She won't hit you.

1437
01:33:22,108 --> 01:33:23,652
She'll probably kill you this time.

1438
01:33:23,677 --> 01:33:24,510
For real?

1439
01:33:25,543 --> 01:33:28,208
Whoa, that looks amazing!

1440
01:33:28,465 --> 01:33:28,847
Hm?

1441
01:33:30,379 --> 01:33:31,554
Why is he here?

1442
01:33:31,626 --> 01:33:33,454
What is that boy doing in our kitchen?

1443
01:33:33,479 --> 01:33:35,036
I want an explanation right now.

1444
01:33:35,094 --> 01:33:35,350
Come on, Mom.

1445
01:33:35,394 --> 01:33:35,876
Get out.

1446
01:33:35,901 --> 01:33:37,225
Don't be like that.

1447
01:33:37,250 --> 01:33:40,297
It's a party, we're supposed to be celebrating!

1448
01:33:40,341 --> 01:33:41,081
Yuzuru.

1449
01:33:41,105 --> 01:33:42,314
You look great.

1450
01:33:49,433 --> 01:33:50,387
Mm.

1451
01:33:51,282 --> 01:33:54,479
You lucked out. Looks like Mom isn't gonna kill you.

1452
01:33:54,746 --> 01:33:55,599
Wow.

1453
01:33:55,660 --> 01:33:57,465
I declare a victory.

1454
01:33:57,490 --> 01:33:59,365
Speaking of winning...

1455
01:33:59,509 --> 01:34:03,395
I submitted some of your photography
to the local contest, Yuzuru.

1456
01:34:03,421 --> 01:34:04,910
Hm? You what?

1457
01:34:04,935 --> 01:34:06,736
It was actually your sister's idea.

1458
01:34:10,709 --> 01:34:13,563
Wha...? But I'm no good, I'm just messing around.

1459
01:34:13,588 --> 01:34:15,249
Oh, come on. That's not true.

1460
01:34:15,862 --> 01:34:18,807
Why would you do this to me?

1461
01:34:19,876 --> 01:34:23,945
Before I forget, next Tuesday you're coming
to see the fireworks with us still, right?

1462
01:34:26,147 --> 01:34:27,496
I-I don't have to.

1463
01:34:27,541 --> 01:34:29,363
You're totally coming.

1464
01:34:41,812 --> 01:34:43,445
Is here okay?

1465
01:34:43,480 --> 01:34:44,525
Yeah, this is good.

1466
01:35:13,647 --> 01:35:15,900
Well, perfect time to go buy snacks.

1467
01:35:16,071 --> 01:35:17,160
Wanna come, Mom?

1468
01:35:29,191 --> 01:35:30,403
Thank you.

1469
01:35:31,227 --> 01:35:34,568
Um, thanks for inviting me over the other day, too.

1470
01:35:34,960 --> 01:35:35,935
Your mom...

1471
01:35:36,707 --> 01:35:38,520
you really think she was happy?

1472
01:35:39,533 --> 01:35:40,584
I couldn't tell.

1473
01:35:42,079 --> 01:35:43,634
Speaking of which,

1474
01:35:43,812 --> 01:35:45,770
I don't know when your birthday is.

1475
01:35:46,989 --> 01:35:50,125
Your birthday was June 7th.

1476
01:35:50,150 --> 01:35:53,360
Oh, no! I missed it. That's too bad.

1477
01:35:53,709 --> 01:35:55,879
I can't believe you're already 18.

1478
01:35:56,214 --> 01:35:58,581
Next year, we'll celebrate together.

1479
01:35:59,060 --> 01:36:00,449
We'll throw a big party.

1480
01:36:01,173 --> 01:36:03,219
I made it sound like we're together.

1481
01:36:27,205 --> 01:36:29,947
I get it now. That makes perfect sense.

1482
01:36:31,220 --> 01:36:32,919
That's why you closed your eyes.

1483
01:36:35,150 --> 01:36:36,946
Huh? Where are you going?

1484
01:36:40,597 --> 01:36:42,313
What, why now?

1485
01:36:42,371 --> 01:36:44,396
The fireworks only just started.

1486
01:36:47,018 --> 01:36:48,370
To go study?

1487
01:36:49,665 --> 01:36:50,547
Okay.

1488
01:36:51,170 --> 01:36:53,363
Well, hey, wait up. I'll walk you home.

1489
01:36:54,688 --> 01:36:55,862
But why?

1490
01:37:02,499 --> 01:37:05,023
Oh, well, see you later.

1491
01:37:15,470 --> 01:37:17,970
Hey, what happened to Shoko?

1492
01:37:19,083 --> 01:37:21,362
Ugh, I forgot my camera!

1493
01:37:21,387 --> 01:37:23,693
Would you mind going back to our place to get it?

1494
01:37:37,047 --> 01:37:38,174
I'm comin' in.

1495
01:37:38,579 --> 01:37:40,008
Man, it's so dark.

1496
01:37:40,281 --> 01:37:41,712
Hey, Shoko, you here?

1497
01:37:41,776 --> 01:37:43,136
It's me, Shoya.

1498
01:37:43,992 --> 01:37:45,167
Good, there it is.

1499
01:37:46,331 --> 01:37:48,987
Mm, I should make sure it's fully charged.

1500
01:37:49,730 --> 01:37:52,369
Huh, you can see the fireworks from here.

1501
01:37:54,116 --> 01:37:56,510
Oh, so that's where she is. Hm?

1502
01:37:57,852 --> 01:38:00,598
What is she...? Hey.

1503
01:38:01,031 --> 01:38:02,639
W-wait a second.

1504
01:38:03,231 --> 01:38:04,533
What is she doing?

1505
01:38:04,758 --> 01:38:05,967
Hey, Shoko.

1506
01:38:09,505 --> 01:38:11,454
Uh, Shoko?

1507
01:38:22,786 --> 01:38:24,152
Don't do it!

1508
01:38:30,409 --> 01:38:31,255
Please no.

1509
01:38:34,095 --> 01:38:35,779
Shoko!

1510
01:39:07,162 --> 01:39:10,035
You have to grab on to the railing.

1511
01:39:10,868 --> 01:39:14,367
Please God, if you give me one more ounce of strength,

1512
01:39:14,718 --> 01:39:16,995
I won't run away from my problems anymore.

1513
01:39:17,911 --> 01:39:20,401
Just do this one thing for me, please.

1514
01:39:21,451 --> 01:39:24,915
Starting tomorrow, I'll look everyone in the eye.

1515
01:39:26,364 --> 01:39:27,592
Starting tomorrow,

1516
01:39:28,379 --> 01:39:30,389
I'll listen when people speak to me.

1517
01:39:31,376 --> 01:39:34,525
Starting tomorrow, I'll be better.

1518
01:39:35,195 --> 01:39:36,947
Shoko.

1519
01:39:39,424 --> 01:39:40,577
There it is.

1520
01:39:40,834 --> 01:39:43,010
The scar I gave her all those years ago.

1521
01:39:43,213 --> 01:39:45,611
Did I ever even apologize for that?

1522
01:39:46,753 --> 01:39:47,667
I'm sorry.

1523
01:39:48,226 --> 01:39:50,010
Sorry for everything, Shoko.

1524
01:39:50,642 --> 01:39:51,978
Are you still mad at me?

1525
01:39:53,641 --> 01:39:54,642
I'm so dumb.

1526
01:39:55,587 --> 01:39:58,121
I should have asked her what she really thinks of me.

1527
01:39:58,805 --> 01:40:00,349
And now I don't know if...

1528
01:40:01,651 --> 01:40:02,779
By the way, Shoko,

1529
01:40:03,445 --> 01:40:04,838
I think that I might...

1530
01:40:17,691 --> 01:40:18,984
Hey there, Sho.

1531
01:40:19,107 --> 01:40:22,110
Your sister whipped you up some of her famous pancakes.

1532
01:40:22,289 --> 01:40:24,776
I'm gonna watch the fireworks!

1533
01:40:36,880 --> 01:40:38,173
It's cold.

1534
01:40:39,143 --> 01:40:40,628
It's warm.

1535
01:41:06,840 --> 01:41:07,995
Mrs. Ishida!

1536
01:41:08,020 --> 01:41:10,195
Ah, what are you doing here?

1537
01:41:11,017 --> 01:41:12,418
I'm glad I caught you.

1538
01:41:12,512 --> 01:41:15,763
I tried calling the salon, but it was closed.

1539
01:41:15,965 --> 01:41:18,315
I just wanted to know about Shoya.

1540
01:41:18,368 --> 01:41:20,517
Well, he's doing a lot better.

1541
01:41:20,591 --> 01:41:22,474
They moved him out of the ICU.

1542
01:41:22,752 --> 01:41:25,644
I was going to his new room. Do you want to come with me?

1543
01:41:25,936 --> 01:41:28,001
Um, do you know if Shoya will...

1544
01:41:28,025 --> 01:41:29,088
Mrs. Ishida.

1545
01:41:29,139 --> 01:41:31,489
Uh, Mrs. Nishimiya.

1546
01:41:32,535 --> 01:41:35,529
I'm sorry for all the trouble Shoya has caused.

1547
01:41:35,554 --> 01:41:38,949
I know what he did in the past
is unforgivable but I want y...

1548
01:41:39,751 --> 01:41:40,977
Please forgive me.

1549
01:41:41,876 --> 01:41:43,613
What on earth are you doing?

1550
01:41:43,638 --> 01:41:44,965
Get up.

1551
01:41:44,990 --> 01:41:46,815
I'm sure Shoya must have done
something, otherwise, this wouldn't've...

1552
01:41:46,840 --> 01:41:47,636
Mrs. Ishida.

1553
01:41:47,661 --> 01:41:51,134
Shoya was trying to save my stupid sister.

1554
01:41:51,354 --> 01:41:54,129
If I had done better...

1555
01:41:54,630 --> 01:41:56,360
She wouldn't have...

1556
01:41:56,598 --> 01:41:58,785
I'm so sorry.

1557
01:41:59,402 --> 01:42:00,507
Please don't.

1558
01:42:01,357 --> 01:42:03,757
Come on, both of you. Please get up.

1559
01:42:03,782 --> 01:42:06,271
I'm just glad that Shoko is okay.

1560
01:42:06,568 --> 01:42:08,413
And you too, Yuzuru.

1561
01:42:09,183 --> 01:42:10,801
So please, get up.

1562
01:42:12,843 --> 01:42:16,246
Why is Shoya lying in a hospital bed instead of you?

1563
01:42:16,446 --> 01:42:19,363
Don't you dare try to play the victim!

1564
01:42:21,188 --> 01:42:22,525
Say something!

1565
01:42:22,775 --> 01:42:26,765
What, you finally felt bad for all
the problems you created for everyone

1566
01:42:26,812 --> 01:42:28,762
so you decided to kill yourself?

1567
01:42:28,787 --> 01:42:31,397
And now all you can say is "I'm sorry"?

1568
01:42:31,422 --> 01:42:32,282
Is that it?

1569
01:42:32,326 --> 01:42:34,371
Well, that's not going to cut it anymore!

1570
01:42:34,483 --> 01:42:35,912
Who do you think you are, huh?

1571
01:42:36,006 --> 01:42:38,400
You're a loser... a deaf loser.

1572
01:42:38,443 --> 01:42:42,084
You sit there in your own little world
and ignore everyone else around you.

1573
01:42:42,136 --> 01:42:44,234
You're the most selfish person I know!

1574
01:42:45,107 --> 01:42:46,120
Ah!

1575
01:42:49,019 --> 01:42:51,139
Hey, who the hell are you?

1576
01:42:55,852 --> 01:42:58,125
You must be the little loser's mother!

1577
01:42:58,205 --> 01:42:58,654
Stop.

1578
01:42:58,678 --> 01:43:02,537
If you can't keep your kid in line
then do us all a favor and stop breathing!

1579
01:43:02,562 --> 01:43:04,048
What are you two doing?

1580
01:43:04,844 --> 01:43:05,921
That's enough.

1581
01:43:09,026 --> 01:43:11,892
I said that's enough. Stop it!

1582
01:43:12,314 --> 01:43:14,800
What is wrong with the both of you?

1583
01:43:25,740 --> 01:43:28,451
Shoko, are you okay?

1584
01:43:36,263 --> 01:43:37,902
I'm sorry!

1585
01:43:43,508 --> 01:43:45,155
I'm so sorry!

1586
01:43:50,873 --> 01:43:52,983
It's all my fault!

1587
01:44:05,194 --> 01:44:06,239
What are you doing?

1588
01:44:07,455 --> 01:44:10,010
I thought if she saw what death looked like,

1589
01:44:10,035 --> 01:44:12,950
she'd stop saying she wanted to kill herself.

1590
01:44:17,297 --> 01:44:21,003
I didn't know what else to do.

1591
01:44:43,444 --> 01:44:44,068
Mm.

1592
01:44:56,815 --> 01:44:57,271
Oh.

1593
01:45:08,168 --> 01:45:11,188
I can't open it. Someone is holding it shut.

1594
01:45:11,254 --> 01:45:13,551
Oh, I didn't notice you there, Shoko.

1595
01:45:13,576 --> 01:45:14,947
Are you, uh, thirsty?

1596
01:45:15,098 --> 01:45:16,824
How about I buy you a drink?

1597
01:45:18,411 --> 01:45:21,234
I heard about what happened with you and Yasho.

1598
01:45:26,062 --> 01:45:28,760
Does this have to do with that stuff on the bridge?

1599
01:45:29,919 --> 01:45:34,217
Yasho was kind and openhearted
enough to accept a guy like me.

1600
01:45:34,368 --> 01:45:36,287
For the first time,

1601
01:45:36,345 --> 01:45:39,368
I know what it feels like to have a true friend.

1602
01:45:43,743 --> 01:45:46,405
Yasho is my best friend in the whole world.

1603
01:45:46,566 --> 01:45:47,930
So I know he'll wake up.

1604
01:45:47,955 --> 01:45:48,986
He just has to.

1605
01:45:55,790 --> 01:45:56,221
Hm?

1606
01:46:02,365 --> 01:46:03,025
Uh.

1607
01:46:06,086 --> 01:46:08,541
You wanted to die because you were suffering?

1608
01:46:08,566 --> 01:46:09,763
What were you thinking?

1609
01:46:09,787 --> 01:46:10,834
Just calm down!

1610
01:46:10,894 --> 01:46:11,929
Everybody's staring.

1611
01:46:11,953 --> 01:46:13,422
I don't care who's listening!

1612
01:46:13,466 --> 01:46:16,435
I have to be loud in order for Shoko to hear me!

1613
01:46:19,716 --> 01:46:22,222
We were all so worried about you.

1614
01:46:22,247 --> 01:46:24,635
I know life can be hard sometimes,

1615
01:46:24,686 --> 01:46:26,577
but it's like that for everyone.

1616
01:46:27,275 --> 01:46:28,232
The thing is,

1617
01:46:28,687 --> 01:46:33,408
you have to accept the bad parts of
yourself with the good and just move forward.

1618
01:46:37,406 --> 01:46:39,342
I'm really glad you're okay.

1619
01:46:42,715 --> 01:46:43,622
I see.

1620
01:46:43,729 --> 01:46:46,084
So you went to see everyone then, huh?

1621
01:46:46,790 --> 01:46:48,118
That's awesome.

1622
01:46:50,217 --> 01:46:53,213
But I'm not as brave as you.

1623
01:46:53,500 --> 01:46:56,479
Even if Shoya does wake up from his coma,

1624
01:46:56,851 --> 01:47:00,233
I think I'd be too ashamed to face him

1625
01:47:00,595 --> 01:47:03,348
'Cause he's right. I haven't changed one bit.

1626
01:47:03,633 --> 01:47:06,245
You needed help and I still wasn't there for you.

1627
01:47:06,402 --> 01:47:08,353
I'm the same coward I've always been.

1628
01:47:09,550 --> 01:47:12,139
You can change. Start now.

1629
01:47:13,844 --> 01:47:15,205
It's not too late.

1630
01:47:18,723 --> 01:47:21,438
I'm really glad you came to see me, Sho.

1631
01:47:47,950 --> 01:47:48,763
Huh?

1632
01:48:02,240 --> 01:48:02,870
Hey!

1633
01:48:03,807 --> 01:48:04,591
Stop it.

1634
01:48:05,334 --> 01:48:06,685
Cut it out.

1635
01:49:44,821 --> 01:49:45,842
No, Shoko!

1636
01:49:48,960 --> 01:49:50,823
What is all this?

1637
01:49:51,052 --> 01:49:53,000
Mom? Hello?

1638
01:49:53,191 --> 01:49:54,679
What's going on?

1639
01:50:02,191 --> 01:50:03,366
Shoko!

1640
01:50:04,846 --> 01:50:06,223
Almost there.

1641
01:50:16,760 --> 01:50:18,181
She isn't here.

1642
01:50:22,729 --> 01:50:24,211
I'm so sorry.

1643
01:50:33,440 --> 01:50:34,183
Huh?

1644
01:50:38,969 --> 01:50:39,575
Yo.

1645
01:51:07,968 --> 01:51:08,472
Hm.

1646
01:51:22,358 --> 01:51:23,937
Hey, why are you crying?

1647
01:51:30,020 --> 01:51:30,504
Hm.

1648
01:51:32,347 --> 01:51:33,512
I'm really glad

1649
01:51:35,898 --> 01:51:36,887
you're okay.

1650
01:51:39,719 --> 01:51:40,995
Don't worry, Shoko.

1651
01:51:41,596 --> 01:51:44,684
I am fine now, I promise.

1652
01:51:45,835 --> 01:51:47,298
Well, more or less.

1653
01:51:48,944 --> 01:51:51,911
So stop looking so gloomy, okay?

1654
01:51:52,779 --> 01:51:53,779
Oh, yeah.

1655
01:51:57,623 --> 01:51:58,896
I wanna tell you...

1656
01:52:00,988 --> 01:52:02,293
that I'm really sorry.

1657
01:52:03,029 --> 01:52:04,605
I never apologized

1658
01:52:05,046 --> 01:52:07,367
for all the stuff I did to you when we were kids.

1659
01:52:08,460 --> 01:52:11,499
Or any of the other stuff afterwards, either.

1660
01:52:12,403 --> 01:52:13,567
So I'm sorry.

1661
01:52:15,621 --> 01:52:16,752
But the thing is,

1662
01:52:17,127 --> 01:52:20,445
even though you were going
through a lot, I was being selfish

1663
01:52:20,970 --> 01:52:22,420
and focused on myself.

1664
01:52:22,843 --> 01:52:24,322
More than anything,

1665
01:52:24,518 --> 01:52:27,764
I wanted to have a conversation with you.

1666
01:52:29,698 --> 01:52:32,557
I wasn't trying to hurt you.

1667
01:52:34,041 --> 01:52:36,310
But I must have, because...

1668
01:52:36,533 --> 01:52:39,208
I made you feel so bad about yourself

1669
01:52:39,474 --> 01:52:42,078
that you decided to go and do the unthinkable.

1670
01:52:42,551 --> 01:52:44,998
No, you're wrong!

1671
01:52:45,023 --> 01:52:47,159
It's because I couldn't change!

1672
01:52:47,184 --> 01:52:48,785
And that's why you fell.

1673
01:52:48,931 --> 01:52:50,058
It's me.

1674
01:52:50,589 --> 01:52:53,793
Everything is always my fault!

1675
01:52:54,801 --> 01:52:58,193
So I thought I should just disappear.

1676
01:52:58,218 --> 01:53:00,120
I was so selfish.

1677
01:53:02,577 --> 01:53:03,893
I'm sorry!

1678
01:53:03,918 --> 01:53:06,452
Please, that's not true. Don't cry.

1679
01:53:09,609 --> 01:53:12,259
Shoko, look at me.

1680
01:53:17,288 --> 01:53:19,856
Did you know we were talking a little while ago?

1681
01:53:20,870 --> 01:53:21,871
I was dreaming.

1682
01:53:22,722 --> 01:53:26,259
And in this dream, I was ready
to just give up on everything.

1683
01:53:27,141 --> 01:53:28,180
I was wrong.

1684
01:53:29,136 --> 01:53:30,217
To be honest,

1685
01:53:31,071 --> 01:53:34,135
I've thought about ending things, just like you did.

1686
01:53:35,211 --> 01:53:37,185
But then I realized something.

1687
01:53:38,212 --> 01:53:41,401
Even though certain things can
make life difficult sometimes,

1688
01:53:42,500 --> 01:53:45,093
that doesn't mean that they're worth dying over.

1689
01:53:46,813 --> 01:53:50,203
I want to apologize and make sure I do it right.

1690
01:53:52,412 --> 01:53:53,339
Shoko?

1691
01:53:54,397 --> 01:53:56,250
I need some help from you.

1692
01:54:00,258 --> 01:54:01,391
I was hoping...

1693
01:54:02,323 --> 01:54:03,672
that maybe you could...

1694
01:54:04,808 --> 01:54:06,194
teach me how to live.

1695
01:54:14,776 --> 01:54:15,887
Please, Shoko.

1696
01:54:37,685 --> 01:54:38,471
Oh, God.

1697
01:54:40,410 --> 01:54:42,727
That's the creepiest thing I've ever said in my life.

1698
01:54:43,766 --> 01:54:45,704
I'm so sorry, just... never mind.

1699
01:54:45,910 --> 01:54:48,564
Forget everything I said, okay? I didn't mean it.

1700
01:55:11,911 --> 01:55:14,926
You have arrived at your destination.

1701
01:55:15,193 --> 01:55:16,493
Hey there, Maria.

1702
01:55:16,518 --> 01:55:19,075
You've become quite the gardener
since I've been gone, huh?

1703
01:55:19,202 --> 01:55:20,419
They're lookin' good.

1704
01:55:21,595 --> 01:55:22,669
Sho-Sho!

1705
01:55:23,299 --> 01:55:24,684
You died!

1706
01:55:24,924 --> 01:55:25,559
You died!

1707
01:55:25,583 --> 01:55:27,117
That's right, Maria.

1708
01:55:27,142 --> 01:55:28,640
Our Sho came back from the dead.

1709
01:55:28,665 --> 01:55:31,128
Don't listen to Grandma. I wasn't really dead.

1710
01:55:31,187 --> 01:55:33,501
Hey look. Isn't that Naoka?

1711
01:55:35,108 --> 01:55:38,849
You know, she was by your side
the entire time you were in a coma.

1712
01:55:39,047 --> 01:55:40,827
You really should thank her.

1713
01:55:43,230 --> 01:55:45,353
My mom said you came to the hospital.

1714
01:55:45,549 --> 01:55:48,508
Listen, I really suck at life sometimes.

1715
01:55:48,942 --> 01:55:51,578
Especially when it comes to stuff like this.

1716
01:55:52,128 --> 01:55:53,005
I just...

1717
01:55:53,393 --> 01:55:55,968
I just can't bring myself to like Shoko.

1718
01:55:56,900 --> 01:55:58,730
I'm probably gonna regret this.

1719
01:55:59,288 --> 01:56:01,538
Remember when you fell in the river?

1720
01:56:01,734 --> 01:56:04,777
It was Kazuki and the guys who pulled you out.

1721
01:56:05,235 --> 01:56:07,495
And then told me not to tell you but...

1722
01:56:08,325 --> 01:56:09,522
Anyway.

1723
01:56:11,067 --> 01:56:12,305
Welcome back.

1724
01:56:12,761 --> 01:56:14,458
Well, I'm gonna take off.

1725
01:56:15,674 --> 01:56:16,942
Thanks, Naoka.

1726
01:56:26,221 --> 01:56:27,356
I don't know.

1727
01:56:27,381 --> 01:56:29,264
Don't you think it's a little short?

1728
01:56:29,289 --> 01:56:31,917
No, no, it looks much cuter like this!

1729
01:56:31,942 --> 01:56:33,410
Oh, you're home, Shoya.

1730
01:56:33,760 --> 01:56:34,799
Oh, hi, Shoya.

1731
01:56:34,823 --> 01:56:36,501
Uh, Mrs. Nishimiya.

1732
01:56:38,160 --> 01:56:39,142
Wait a minute.

1733
01:56:39,238 --> 01:56:40,085
Yes?

1734
01:56:41,222 --> 01:56:42,415
I'm really sorry.

1735
01:56:42,513 --> 01:56:44,748
Uh, yeah. Me too.

1736
01:56:44,904 --> 01:56:47,470
No matter what, my son always bounces right back.

1737
01:56:47,495 --> 01:56:48,302
See ya later, Mom.

1738
01:56:48,327 --> 01:56:49,935
I'm heading out to pick up Maria now.

1739
01:56:50,057 --> 01:56:51,011
Okay!

1740
01:56:51,196 --> 01:56:51,816
Who's that?

1741
01:56:51,841 --> 01:56:54,782
That's my son-in-law. He's back from being deployed.

1742
01:56:54,807 --> 01:56:55,822
Oh, Shoya.

1743
01:56:56,189 --> 01:56:58,124
Yuzuru is waiting for you upstairs.

1744
01:56:58,220 --> 01:56:59,919
Give her the jelly that's in the fridge.

1745
01:57:01,457 --> 01:57:01,974
Yo.

1746
01:57:01,998 --> 01:57:02,972
Whoa.

1747
01:57:03,397 --> 01:57:04,441
New threads?

1748
01:57:04,466 --> 01:57:05,597
It looks good on you.

1749
01:57:05,780 --> 01:57:07,170
Check it out. I won.

1750
01:57:07,314 --> 01:57:08,619
Huh? Wow!

1751
01:57:08,644 --> 01:57:10,326
No kidding. Impressive.

1752
01:57:10,351 --> 01:57:11,861
Now feast your eyes on this.

1753
01:57:11,885 --> 01:57:12,668
Whoa.

1754
01:57:13,033 --> 01:57:14,411
Not so impressive.

1755
01:57:14,436 --> 01:57:15,698
Since you're alive again,

1756
01:57:15,723 --> 01:57:18,319
will you please help teach me how to study?

1757
01:57:18,344 --> 01:57:19,650
Of course, no prob.

1758
01:57:23,272 --> 01:57:25,737
So, uh, you're giving school another shot?

1759
01:57:25,878 --> 01:57:28,901
Yeah, I decided to take a cue from Shoko.

1760
01:57:30,189 --> 01:57:33,168
I figured the least I can do is try.

1761
01:57:33,767 --> 01:57:35,579
I don't wanna let anyone down.

1762
01:57:37,826 --> 01:57:40,241
Isn't your big school festival tomorrow?

1763
01:57:40,266 --> 01:57:41,461
Oh yeah, that's right.

1764
01:57:50,750 --> 01:57:52,947
Ah, good morning, everybody!

1765
01:57:52,972 --> 01:57:54,333
Up top, yeah!

1766
01:57:54,644 --> 01:57:55,815
Ha, ha, ha!

1767
01:57:56,218 --> 01:57:58,772
I said horrible things and I'm sorry.

1768
01:58:06,957 --> 01:58:07,588
Okay.

1769
01:58:08,230 --> 01:58:09,158
I'm heading out.

1770
01:58:09,182 --> 01:58:10,677
Have a good day, sweetheart.

1771
01:58:10,702 --> 01:58:14,482
Oh, I see now. So that's what you're
supposed to do with those things.

1772
01:58:14,507 --> 01:58:15,324
What's that?

1773
01:58:15,349 --> 01:58:17,471
Oh, nothing. I'll see you later, 'kay?

1774
01:58:17,852 --> 01:58:20,034
Have a good day, Sho-Sho!

1775
01:58:34,863 --> 01:58:36,615
Ha! There you are.

1776
01:58:40,128 --> 01:58:41,447
Okay, let's go.

1777
01:58:50,839 --> 01:58:52,258
Isn't that Shoya?

1778
01:58:53,185 --> 01:58:54,026
Who is that?

1779
01:58:54,051 --> 01:58:55,916
Wait the one who was in the hospital, right?

1780
01:58:55,941 --> 01:58:57,101
The guy who jumped?

1781
01:59:02,389 --> 01:59:04,649
You probably didn't know this, but I...

1782
01:59:05,734 --> 01:59:07,560
don't really fit in at school.

1783
01:59:10,501 --> 01:59:12,615
It's cause I have trouble

1784
01:59:12,965 --> 01:59:14,702
looking people in the eye.

1785
01:59:15,650 --> 01:59:19,281
So it's easier for me to just
stare at the floor all the time.

1786
01:59:22,395 --> 01:59:24,388
You think it's okay to do that?

1787
01:59:26,688 --> 01:59:28,307
Uh, Shoko.

1788
01:59:28,648 --> 01:59:31,424
I can actually do it without you leading me.

1789
01:59:31,923 --> 01:59:32,872
But thank you.

1790
01:59:33,926 --> 01:59:35,502
This is my classroom here.

1791
01:59:37,323 --> 01:59:38,987
Has the water boiled yet?

1792
01:59:39,011 --> 01:59:40,345
Just a few more minutes.

1793
01:59:41,173 --> 01:59:43,920
Oh, wow. Shoya's back at school!

1794
01:59:43,945 --> 01:59:45,338
Are you okay now?

1795
01:59:47,425 --> 01:59:48,862
You know what?

1796
01:59:49,385 --> 01:59:52,229
I think my stomach's acting up a bit.

1797
01:59:52,359 --> 01:59:54,889
So, sorry.

1798
01:59:54,914 --> 01:59:57,010
Yasho! Huh?

1799
02:00:09,302 --> 02:00:10,303
Yasho?

1800
02:00:10,691 --> 02:00:13,737
Huh? Oh, hey. That you, Nagatsuka?

1801
02:00:13,802 --> 02:00:15,558
You feeling okay?

1802
02:00:18,523 --> 02:00:19,625
Yasho.

1803
02:00:20,108 --> 02:00:22,382
Good morning, Nagatsuka. Good to see you.

1804
02:00:22,407 --> 02:00:23,722
So how is everything?

1805
02:00:23,823 --> 02:00:24,743
About the...?

1806
02:00:24,767 --> 02:00:25,615
What's going on?

1807
02:00:25,877 --> 02:00:27,102
Why won't you look at me?

1808
02:00:27,269 --> 02:00:29,540
I don't know. I just feel weird.

1809
02:00:30,219 --> 02:00:33,595
I made myself a promise I would
look people in the eyes from now on.

1810
02:00:34,203 --> 02:00:35,476
Guess I'm too chicken.

1811
02:00:35,594 --> 02:00:37,231
Hey, Yasho.

1812
02:00:37,840 --> 02:00:38,877
Shoya!

1813
02:00:39,864 --> 02:00:43,430
You're okay. I'm glad.

1814
02:00:43,878 --> 02:00:46,886
'Cause if you... if you didn't wake up,

1815
02:00:46,911 --> 02:00:48,732
I didn't know what I would do!

1816
02:00:48,757 --> 02:00:50,498
You're everything to me.

1817
02:00:50,523 --> 02:00:52,320
I would have been all alone.

1818
02:00:52,599 --> 02:00:56,283
Listen, the stuff on the bridge,
don't worry about it, 'kay?

1819
02:00:56,676 --> 02:01:00,400
Friends say stuff they don't mean to
each other all the time. It doesn't matter.

1820
02:01:01,095 --> 02:01:04,310
I'm begging you, don't ever leave us again.

1821
02:01:04,738 --> 02:01:06,871
Promise me. I can't lose you.

1822
02:01:06,896 --> 02:01:08,077
It's gonna be okay.

1823
02:01:09,978 --> 02:01:10,892
Hey, look.

1824
02:01:11,396 --> 02:01:12,352
I'm sorry.

1825
02:01:13,015 --> 02:01:13,903
I mean...

1826
02:01:15,096 --> 02:01:15,971
Thank you.

1827
02:01:16,891 --> 02:01:17,984
For being a friend.

1828
02:01:18,531 --> 02:01:19,706
You've very welcome.

1829
02:01:19,731 --> 02:01:20,910
But, uh...

1830
02:01:21,246 --> 02:01:22,634
What's up with the facial hair?

1831
02:01:22,897 --> 02:01:24,622
That's my lucky 'stache.

1832
02:01:24,647 --> 02:01:27,623
I swore I wasn't shaving it till you woke up.

1833
02:01:27,764 --> 02:01:29,123
You did that for me?

1834
02:01:33,714 --> 02:01:34,374
Uh.

1835
02:01:35,385 --> 02:01:36,527
What's going on?

1836
02:01:36,552 --> 02:01:39,302
We heard Nagatsuka howling your name, so we followed it.

1837
02:01:41,721 --> 02:01:42,548
I-I see.

1838
02:01:43,344 --> 02:01:45,902
Miki, did you bring the stuff to give to Shoya?

1839
02:01:47,567 --> 02:01:50,135
I brought them, but I can't give it to him.

1840
02:01:50,160 --> 02:01:51,625
It's a total failure.

1841
02:01:51,650 --> 02:01:53,518
Don't be silly, hand 'em over.

1842
02:01:59,923 --> 02:02:00,789
Here.

1843
02:02:01,001 --> 02:02:01,848
Hm?

1844
02:02:02,167 --> 02:02:04,343
There was supposed to be a thousand of them,

1845
02:02:04,440 --> 02:02:06,632
but we couldn't finish it fast enough.

1846
02:02:07,166 --> 02:02:11,721
Everyone worked really hard and
did their best, but we just couldn't.

1847
02:02:11,746 --> 02:02:13,428
No, this is amazing!

1848
02:02:13,453 --> 02:02:14,690
It's more than enough.

1849
02:02:14,777 --> 02:02:17,006
No one's ever done anything like this for me.

1850
02:02:17,074 --> 02:02:18,975
It really means a lot, seriously.

1851
02:02:19,428 --> 02:02:20,847
Thank you, Miki.

1852
02:02:21,133 --> 02:02:22,736
Also, sorry.

1853
02:02:23,175 --> 02:02:24,306
And to you, too.

1854
02:02:24,667 --> 02:02:26,930
No worries. It's all good, bro.

1855
02:02:27,835 --> 02:02:30,993
Ugh, enough! All this sappy talk.

1856
02:02:31,276 --> 02:02:32,550
I'm gonna lose my lunch.

1857
02:02:32,575 --> 02:02:35,003
Why do you always have to be like that, Naoka?

1858
02:02:35,334 --> 02:02:37,900
What, you got a problem with me or something?

1859
02:02:37,925 --> 02:02:38,883
You pickin' a fight?

1860
02:02:38,908 --> 02:02:41,152
Okay, everybody just calm down.

1861
02:02:41,962 --> 02:02:42,852
Shoya.

1862
02:02:43,323 --> 02:02:45,187
Listen, I'm really sorry.

1863
02:02:45,561 --> 02:02:48,477
After all you'd been through, you really needed a friend.

1864
02:02:49,389 --> 02:02:51,096
But all I did was run away.

1865
02:02:52,526 --> 02:02:53,396
That's okay.

1866
02:02:54,286 --> 02:02:55,504
I did the same thing.

1867
02:02:57,033 --> 02:03:00,191
Stop acting so worried. They're just talking things out.

1868
02:03:02,696 --> 02:03:04,001
You apologizing?

1869
02:03:05,387 --> 02:03:08,173
Well, guess that's all you know how to do.

1870
02:03:08,846 --> 02:03:10,848
Moron.

1871
02:03:15,263 --> 02:03:16,829
Moron.

1872
02:03:17,613 --> 02:03:18,704
Moron.

1873
02:03:19,291 --> 02:03:19,876
Mm.

1874
02:03:26,040 --> 02:03:28,344
Whatever. I'm gonna go find something to eat.

1875
02:03:28,369 --> 02:03:29,802
Did she just run away?

1876
02:03:29,827 --> 02:03:31,229
I think she's embarrassed.

1877
02:03:34,266 --> 02:03:37,343
Hey, guys. I have a big favor to ask all of you.

1878
02:03:38,169 --> 02:03:38,900
That okay?

1879
02:03:40,585 --> 02:03:43,470
Do you wanna go together to the festival?

1880
02:03:43,783 --> 02:03:44,745
